capwapMIB.description: Copyright (C) 2007 The Internet Society. This version of the MIB module is part of RFC xxx; see the RFC itself for full legal notices. This MIB module contains managed object definitions for the CAPWAP Protocol.

CapwapWTPId.name: CapwapWTPId
CapwapWTPId.description: Represents a unique identifier of a WTP instance.

CapwapStationId.name: CapwapStationId
CapwapStationId.description: Represents a unique identifier of a station instance.

CapwapRadioId.name: CapwapRadioId
CapwapRadioId.description: Represents a unique identifier of a radio on a WTP.

CapwapWTPTunnelMode.name: CapwapWTPTunnelMode
CapwapWTPTunnelMode.description: Represents the tunneling mode for station data that are supported by the WTP. The possible value could be: localBridging(1) - Local Bridging Mode, dot3Tunnel(2) - 802.3 Frame Tunnel Mode, nativeTunnel(3) - Native Frame Tunnel Mode.
CapwapWTPTunnelMode.reference: Section 4.6.41. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.

CapwapWTPMACType.name: CapwapWTPMACType
CapwapWTPMACType.description: Represents the MAC mode of operation supported by the WTP. The possible value could be: localMAC(1) - Local-MAC Mode, splitMAC(2) - Split-MAC Mode.
CapwapWTPMACType.reference: Section 4.6.44. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.

CapwapWTPRadioTemplateIfIndex.name: CapwapWTPRadioTemplateIfIndex
CapwapWTPRadioTemplateIfIndex.description: Represents the TC for a ifindex of 'WTP radio template' interface type.

CapwapChannelType.name: CapwapChannelType
CapwapChannelType.description: Represents the channel type for CAPWAP protocol. The following values are supported: data(1) - data Channel control(2) - control Channel.

CapwapWTPAuthenMethod.name: CapwapWTPAuthenMethod
CapwapWTPAuthenMethod.description: The attribute represents the authentication credential type for WTP. The following values are supported: clear(1) - cleartext and no authentication, x509(2) - X.509 Certificate Based, psk(3) - Pre-Shared Secret, other(8) - Other method, for example, vendor specific. As mandatory requirement, CAPWAP control channel authentication should use DTLS, and either by certificate or PSK. For data channel, DTLS is optional.

capwapACWTPSessions.name: capwapACWTPSessions
capwapACWTPSessions.reference: Section 4.6.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapACWTPSessions.description: Represents the total number of WTPs which are connecting to AC.

capwapACWTPSessionsLimit.name: capwapACWTPSessionsLimit
capwapACWTPSessionsLimit.reference: Section 4.6.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapACWTPSessionsLimit.description: Represents the maximum number of WTP sessions supported by the AC.

capwapACStationSessions.name: capwapACStationSessions
capwapACStationSessions.reference: Section 4.6.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapACStationSessions.description: Represents the total number of stations which are accessing the wireless service.

capwapACStationSessionsLimit.name: capwapACStationSessionsLimit
capwapACStationSessionsLimit.reference: Section 4.6.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapACStationSessionsLimit.description: Represents the maximum number of station sessions supported by the AC.

capwapACDataChannelSecOptions.name: capwapACDataChannelSecOptions
capwapACDataChannelSecOptions.reference: Section 4.6.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapACDataChannelSecOptions.description: Represents the security policy supported for CAPWAP data channel. The AC MAY support more than one option, represented by the bit field below. clear(1) - Clear Text, dtls(2) - DTLS, vendor(3) - vendor specific.

capwapACWTPAuthenOptions.name: capwapACWTPAuthenOptions
capwapACWTPAuthenOptions.reference: Section 4.6.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapACWTPAuthenOptions.description: Represents the authentication credentia type supported by the AC for control channel. The AC MAY support more than one option, represented by the bit field below. x509(1) - X.509 Certificate Based psk(2) - Pre-Shared Secret.

capwapACHwVersion.name: capwapACHwVersion
capwapACHwVersion.reference: Section 4.6.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapACHwVersion.description: Represents the AC's hardware version number.

capwapACSwVersion.name: capwapACSwVersion
capwapACSwVersion.reference: Section 4.6.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapACSwVersion.description: Represents the AC's software version number.

capwapWTPFallbackEnable.name: capwapWTPFallbackEnable
capwapWTPFallbackEnable.reference: Section 4.6.40. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPFallbackEnable.description: Represents enable or disable automatic CAPWAP fallback in the event that a WTP detects its preferred AC, and is not currently connected to it.

capwapWTPACNameList.name: capwapWTPACNameList
capwapWTPACNameList.reference: Section 4.6.5. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPACNameList.description: Represent the name list of ACs and use semicolon to separate AC name. The AC name could be configured with the order of Primary AC, secondary AC and so on. WTP will try to connect to AC name in the list one by one till it connected to one AC.

capwapMaxFailedDTLSSessionRetry.name: capwapMaxFailedDTLSSessionRetry
capwapMaxFailedDTLSSessionRetry.reference: Section 4.7.7. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapMaxFailedDTLSSessionRetry.description: Represent the maximum number of failed DTLS session establishment attempts before the CAPWAP device enters a silent period.

capwapWTPIdleTimeout.name: capwapWTPIdleTimeout
capwapWTPIdleTimeout.reference: Section 4.8.5. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPIdleTimeout.description: Represent the time out parameter for WTP idle state.

capwapWTPMaxDiscoveries.name: capwapWTPMaxDiscoveries
capwapWTPMaxDiscoveries.reference: Section 4.8.6. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPMaxDiscoveries.description: Represent the maximum number of Discovery Request messages that will be sent after a WTP boots

capwapWTPMaxRetransmit.name: capwapWTPMaxRetransmit
capwapWTPMaxRetransmit.reference: Section 4.8.7. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPMaxRetransmit.description: Represent the maximum number of retransmissions for a given CAPWAP packet before the link layer considers the peer dead.

capwapWTPReportInterval.name: capwapWTPReportInterval
capwapWTPReportInterval.reference: Section 4.8.8. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPReportInterval.description: Represents the interval for WTP send report.

capwapWTPStateTable.name: capwapWTPStateTable
capwapWTPStateTable.description: This table provides the state information for WTPs which are accessing to AC via CAPWAP protocol.

capwapWTPStateEntry.name: capwapWTPStateEntry
capwapWTPStateEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by AC for each WTPs which are accessing to AC via CAPWAP protocol.

capwapWTPId.name: capwapWTPId
capwapWTPId.description: Represents the identifier of a WTP.

capwapWTPIPAddress.name: capwapWTPIPAddress
capwapWTPIPAddress.description: Represents the IP address of a WTP.

capwapWTPSerialId.name: capwapWTPSerialId
capwapWTPSerialId.reference: Section 4.6.38. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPSerialId.description: Represents the serial number of a WTP.

capwapWTPState.name: capwapWTPState
capwapWTPState.reference: Section 2.3.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPState.description: Represents WTP current state according to CAPWAP protocol's FSM. The following values are supported: dtls(1) - DTLS negotiation process join(2) - WTP is joining with AC, image(3) - WTP is downloading software, configure(4) - WTP is getting configuration for AC, run(5) - WTP come to run state, clear(6) - WTP is recovery default configuration.

capwapWTPTable.name: capwapWTPTable
capwapWTPTable.description: The table provides information for WTPs in running state.

capwapWTPEntry.name: capwapWTPEntry
capwapWTPEntry.description: An entry in this table is created by AC during CAPWAP protocol process.

capwapWTPCurrId.name: capwapWTPCurrId
capwapWTPCurrId.description: Represents the unique identifier of a WTP Which is in running state.

capwapWTPName.name: capwapWTPName
capwapWTPName.reference: Section 4.6.45. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPName.description: Represents the name of a WTP.

capwapWTPLocation.name: capwapWTPLocation
capwapWTPLocation.reference: Section 4.6.28. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPLocation.description: Represents the name of a WTP.

capwapWTPManufacturerId.name: capwapWTPManufacturerId
capwapWTPManufacturerId.reference: Section 4.6.39. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPManufacturerId.description: SMI Network Management Private Enterprise Codes, which are assigned by the IANA. NMS could know which vendor manufactures the WTP.

capwapWTPModelId.name: capwapWTPModelId
capwapWTPModelId.reference: Section 4.6.38. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.

capwapWTPBoardId.name: capwapWTPBoardId
capwapWTPBoardId.reference: Section 4.6.38. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.

capwapWTPBoardRevision.name: capwapWTPBoardRevision
capwapWTPBoardRevision.reference: Section 4.6.38. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPBoardRevision.description: Represents the revision number of the board.

capwapWTPBaseMACAddress.name: capwapWTPBaseMACAddress
capwapWTPBaseMACAddress.reference: Section 4.6.38. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPBaseMACAddress.description: Represents the WTP's Base MAC Address, which MAY be assigned to the primary Ethernet interface.

capwapWTPTunnelModeOptions.name: capwapWTPTunnelModeOptions
capwapWTPTunnelModeOptions.reference: Section 4.6.41. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPTunnelModeOptions.description: Represents the tunneling modes for station data that are supported by the WTP. The WTP MAY support more than one option, represented by the bit field below. localBridging(1) - Local Bridging Mode, dot3Tunnel(2) - 802.3 Frame Tunnel Mode, nativeTunnel(3) - Native Frame Tunnel Mode.

capwapWTPMACTypeOptions.name: capwapWTPMACTypeOptions
capwapWTPMACTypeOptions.reference: Section 4.6.44. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPMACTypeOptions.description: Represents the MAC mode of operation supported by the WTP. The WTP MAY support more than one option, represented by the bit field below. localMAC(1) - Local-MAC Mode, splitMAC(2) - Split-MAC Mode.

capwapWTPDiscoveryType.name: capwapWTPDiscoveryType
capwapWTPDiscoveryType.reference: Section 4.6.20. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPDiscoveryType.description: Represents how WTP discovered the AC. The following values are supported: unknown(1) - the method is unknown, staticConfig(2) - static IP configuration, dhcp(3) - DHCP, dns(4) - DNS, acRef(5) - AC Referral.

capwapWTPRadiosInUseNumber.name: capwapWTPRadiosInUseNumber
capwapWTPRadiosInUseNumber.reference: Section 4.6.39. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPRadiosInUseNumber.description: Represents the number of radios which are in use.

capwapWTPRadioNumLimit.name: capwapWTPRadioNumLimit
capwapWTPRadioNumLimit.reference: Section 4.6.39. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPRadioNumLimit.description: Represents the maximum radio number could be supported by WTP.

capwapWTPSwVersion.name: capwapWTPSwVersion
capwapWTPSwVersion.reference: Section 4.6.39. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPSwVersion.description: Represents the name of WTP software.

capwapWTPSwSize.name: capwapWTPSwSize
capwapWTPSwSize.reference: Section 9.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPSwSize.description: Represents the size of WTP software.

capwapWTPHwVersion.name: capwapWTPHwVersion
capwapWTPHwVersion.reference: Section 4.6.39. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPHwVersion.description: Represents the version of WTP hardware.

capwapWTPStaticIPEnable.name: capwapWTPStaticIPEnable
capwapWTPStaticIPEnable.reference: Section 4.6.49. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPStaticIPEnable.description: Represents whether the WTP should use a static IP address or not. A value of zero disables the static IP address, while a value of one enables it.

capwapWTPStaticIP.name: capwapWTPStaticIP
capwapWTPStaticIP.reference: Section 4.6.49. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPStaticIP.description: When capwapWTPStaticIPEnable is true, it represents the static IP address to assign to the WTP.

capwapWTPNetmask.name: capwapWTPNetmask
capwapWTPNetmask.reference: Section 4.6.49. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPNetmask.description: When capwapWTPStaticIPEnable is true, it represents the netmask to assign to the WTP.

capwapWTPGateway.name: capwapWTPGateway
capwapWTPGateway.reference: Section 4.6.49. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPGateway.description: When capwapWTPStaticIPEnable is true, it represents the gateway to assign to the WTP.

capwapRadioTable.name: capwapRadioTable
capwapRadioTable.description: The table will describe WTP and radio's relation-ship.

capwapRadioEntry.name: capwapRadioEntry
capwapRadioEntry.description: Each entry contains each radio's information for a specific WTP.

capwapRadioId.name: capwapRadioId
capwapRadioId.reference: Section 4.6.31. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioId.description: Represents the identifier of a radio on a WTP, and only requires unique on a WTP. For example, WTP A and WTP B will use same value for capwapRadioId for their first radio.

capwapWTPRadioTemplateIfIndex.name: capwapWTPRadioTemplateIfIndex
capwapWTPRadioTemplateIfIndex.description: Represents the ifindex for a interface of 'WTP radio template' interface type. Before WTPs connect to AC and get configuration, administrator will prepare configuration for them. For radio related configuration, administrator could create a logical interface in 'WTP radio template' interface type, and configure radio parameter under it. The configuration and statistic paramter depend on wireless binding type for radio. The 'WTP radio template interface' provides a way to uniquely identify each radio by logical at AC side. As most MIBs use ifindex to identify a interface for configuration and statistic data, for example, 802.11 MIB, it will be very easy to reuse other MIBs like 802.11 MIB by this way. Require IANA to assign a ifType for 'WTP radio template'.

capwapWirelessBinding.name: capwapWirelessBinding
capwapWirelessBinding.reference: Section 4.3. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWirelessBinding.description: Represents the wireless binding type for radio. The following values are supported: none(1) - No any wireless bingding defined. dot11(2) - IEEE 802.11. dot16(3) - IEEE 802.16. epc(4) - EPCGlobal.

capwapAdminStatusEnable.name: capwapAdminStatusEnable
capwapAdminStatusEnable.reference: Section 4.6.31. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapAdminStatusEnable.description: Represents the administrator status of radio, whether it is enabled or not.

capwapOperStatus.name: capwapOperStatus
capwapOperStatus.reference: Section 4.6.32. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapOperStatus.description: Represents the operational status of radio, whether it is enabled or not.

capwapStationTable.name: capwapStationTable
capwapStationTable.description: This table contains the information of stations which are associating with the specific radio on the WTP.

capwapStationEntry.name: capwapStationEntry
capwapStationEntry.description: Each entry contains information of each station's association information.

capwapStationId.name: capwapStationId
capwapStationId.reference: Section 4.6.8. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapStationId.description: Represents the identifier of the station.

capwapStationAddedTime.name: capwapStationAddedTime
capwapStationAddedTime.reference: Section 4.6.8. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapStationAddedTime.description: This is the time stamp for the very first time when the station is added.

capwapStationVlanName.name: capwapStationVlanName
capwapStationVlanName.reference: Section 4.6.8. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapStationVlanName.description: Represents Vlan name to which the station is associated.

capwapWTPRebootStatsTable.name: capwapWTPRebootStatsTable
capwapWTPRebootStatsTable.description: The table will provide WTP reboot statistic data.

capwapWTPRebootStatsEntry.name: capwapWTPRebootStatsEntry
capwapWTPRebootStatsEntry.description: Each entry of the table will provide the reboot statistic data for a specific WTP.

capwapWTPRebootCount.name: capwapWTPRebootCount
capwapWTPRebootCount.reference: Section 4.6.48. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPRebootCount.description: Represents the number of reboots that have occurred due to a WTP crash. A value of 65535 implies that this information is not available on the WTP.

capwapWTPInitCount.name: capwapWTPInitCount
capwapWTPInitCount.reference: Section 4.6.48. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPInitCount.description: Represents the number of reboots that have occurred at the request of a CAPWAP protocol message, such as a change in configuration that required a reboot or an explicit CAPWAP protocol reset request. A value of 65535 implies that this information is not available on the WTP.

capwapWTPLinkFailureCount.name: capwapWTPLinkFailureCount
capwapWTPLinkFailureCount.reference: Section 4.6.48. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPLinkFailureCount.description: Represents the number of times that a CAPWAP protocol connection with an AC has failed due to link failure.

capwapWTPSwFailureCount.name: capwapWTPSwFailureCount
capwapWTPSwFailureCount.reference: Section 4.6.48. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPSwFailureCount.description: Represents the number of times that a CAPWAP protocol connection with an AC has failed due to software related reasons.

capwapWTPHwFailureCount.name: capwapWTPHwFailureCount
capwapWTPHwFailureCount.reference: Section 4.6.48. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPHwFailureCount.description: Represents the number of times that a CAPWAP protocol connection with an AC has failed due to hardware related reasons.

capwapWTPOtherFailureCount.name: capwapWTPOtherFailureCount
capwapWTPOtherFailureCount.reference: Section 4.6.48. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPOtherFailureCount.description: Represents the number of times that a CAPWAP protocol connection with an AC has failed due to known reasons, other than AC initiated, link, sofware or hardware failure.

capwapWTPUnknownFailureCount.name: capwapWTPUnknownFailureCount
capwapWTPUnknownFailureCount.reference: Section 4.6.48. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPUnknownFailureCount.description: Represents the number of times that a CAPWAP protocol connection with an AC has failed for unknown reasons.

capwapWTPLastFailureType.name: capwapWTPLastFailureType
capwapWTPLastFailureType.reference: Section 4.6.48. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPLastFailureType.description: The failure type of the most recent WTP failure. The following values are supported: notSupport(1) - Not Supported, acInit(2) - AC Initiated, linkFailure(3) - Link Failure, swFailure(4) - Software Failure, hwFailure(5) - Hardware Failure, otherFailure(6) - Other Failure, unknown(255) - Unknown (e.g., WTP doesn't keep track of info).

capwapRadioStatsTable.name: capwapRadioStatsTable
capwapRadioStatsTable.description: The table provides statistics on radio behavior and reasons why the WTP radio has been reset.

capwapRadioStatsEntry.name: capwapRadioStatsEntry
capwapRadioStatsEntry.description: Each entry of the table will provide the statistic data of event happend on a specific radio of a WTP.

capwapRadioResetCount.name: capwapRadioResetCount
capwapRadioResetCount.reference: Section 4.6.47. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioResetCount.description: Represents the number of times that that the radio has been reset.

capwapRadioSwFailCount.name: capwapRadioSwFailCount
capwapRadioSwFailCount.reference: Section 4.6.47. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioSwFailCount.description: Represents the number of times that the radio has failed due to software related reasons.

capwapRadioHwFailCount.name: capwapRadioHwFailCount
capwapRadioHwFailCount.reference: Section 4.6.47. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioHwFailCount.description: Represents the number of times that the radio has failed due to hardware related reasons.

capwapRadioOtherFailCount.name: capwapRadioOtherFailCount
capwapRadioOtherFailCount.reference: Section 4.6.47. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioOtherFailCount.description: Represents the number of times that the radio has failed due to known reasons, other than software or hardware failure.

capwapRadioUnknownFailCount.name: capwapRadioUnknownFailCount
capwapRadioUnknownFailCount.reference: Section 4.6.47. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioUnknownFailCount.description: Represents the number of times that the radio has failed for unknown reasons.

capwapRadioConfigUpdateCount.name: capwapRadioConfigUpdateCount
capwapRadioConfigUpdateCount.reference: Section 4.6.47. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioConfigUpdateCount.description: Represents the number of times that the radio configuration has been updated.

capwapRadioChannelChangeCount.name: capwapRadioChannelChangeCount
capwapRadioChannelChangeCount.reference: Section 4.6.47. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioChannelChangeCount.description: Represents the number of times that the radio channel has been changed.

capwapRadioBandChangeCount.name: capwapRadioBandChangeCount
capwapRadioBandChangeCount.reference: Section 4.6.47. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioBandChangeCount.description: Represents the number of times that the radio has changed frequency bands.

capwapRadioCurrentNoiseFloor.name: capwapRadioCurrentNoiseFloor
capwapRadioCurrentNoiseFloor.description: Represents the noise floor of the radio receiver in units of dBm.

capwapRadioDecryptErrorCount.name: capwapRadioDecryptErrorCount
capwapRadioDecryptErrorCount.reference: Section 4.6.47. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioDecryptErrorCount.description: Represents the number of decryption errors that occurred on the WTP. Note that this field is only valid in cases where the WTP provides encryption/decryption services.

capwapRadioTxQueueLevel.name: capwapRadioTxQueueLevel
capwapRadioTxQueueLevel.reference: Section 4.6.46. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioTxQueueLevel.description: Represents the percentage of Wireless Transmit queue utilization,calaculated as the sum of utilized transmit queue lengths divided by the sum of maximum transmit queue lengths, multiplied by 100.

capwapRadioRFLinkFramesPerSec.name: capwapRadioRFLinkFramesPerSec
capwapRadioRFLinkFramesPerSec.reference: Section 4.6.46. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioRFLinkFramesPerSec.description: Represents the number of frames transmitted or received per second by the WTP over the aur interface.

capwapRadioLastFailType.name: capwapRadioLastFailType
capwapRadioLastFailType.description: Represents the failure type of the most recent radio failure. The following values are supported: notSupport(1) - Not Supported, swFailure(2) - Software Failure, hwFailure(3) - Hardware Failure, otherFailure(4) - Other Failure, unknown(255) - Unknown.

capwapChannelUp.name: capwapChannelUp
capwapChannelUp.description: This notification is sent by AC when a CAPWAP channel established.The notification is separated for data or control channel.

capwapChannelDown.name: capwapChannelDown
capwapChannelDown.description: This notification is sent by AC when CAPWAP channel becomes down.

capwapDecryptErrorReport.name: capwapDecryptErrorReport
capwapDecryptErrorReport.description: This notification is generated when a WTP that has occurred decryption error since the last report.
capwapDecryptErrorReport.reference: Section 4.6.15. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.

capwapJoinFailure.name: capwapJoinFailure
capwapJoinFailure.description: This notification is generated when a WTP fails to join.
capwapJoinFailure.reference: Section 4.6.33. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.

capwapImageUpgradeFailure.name: capwapImageUpgradeFailure
capwapImageUpgradeFailure.description: This notification is generated when a WTP fails to update software image.
capwapImageUpgradeFailure.reference: Section 4.6.33. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.

capwapConfigMsgError.name: capwapConfigMsgError
capwapConfigMsgError.description: This notification is generated when a WTP received message elements in the Configuration Status Response which it was unable to apply locally.
capwapConfigMsgError.reference: Section 4.6.34. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.

capwapRadioOperableStatus.name: capwapRadioOperableStatus
capwapRadioOperableStatus.description: The notification will notify which radio become inoperable or operable.
capwapRadioOperableStatus.reference: Section 4.6.32. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.

capwapWTPAuthenticationFailure.name: capwapWTPAuthenticationFailure
capwapWTPAuthenticationFailure.description: The notification will notify the authentication failure event, and provides the reason for it.
capwapWTPAuthenticationFailure.reference: Section 2.3.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.

capwapChannelType.name: capwapChannelType
capwapChannelType.description: Represents the channel type for CAPWAP protocol.

capwapChannelDownReason.name: capwapChannelDownReason
capwapChannelDownReason.description: Represents the reason for Channel down. The following values are supported: timeout(1) - The keep alive is timeout, rekeyfailure(2) - Rekey process is failed, channel will be broken. apReboot(3) - AC reboot WTP.

capwapIdEntryNum.name: capwapIdEntryNum
capwapIdEntryNum.reference: Section 4.6.15. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapIdEntryNum.description: Represents the entry number of station id in the capwapStationIdList.

capwapStationIdList.name: capwapStationIdList
capwapStationIdList.reference: Section 4.6.15. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapStationIdList.description: Represents the list of station id.

capwapWTPAuthenFailureReason.name: capwapWTPAuthenFailureReason
capwapWTPAuthenFailureReason.reference: Section 2.3.1. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapWTPAuthenFailureReason.description: Represents reason for WTP authorization failure. The following values are supported: keyMismatch(1) - WTP's and AC's key is not matched, invalidCA(2) - ca is not valide, micError(3) - detect mic error, timeout(4) - WaitDTLS Timer is timeout, unknown(8) - Unknown reason.

capwapRadioOperStatusFlag.name: capwapRadioOperStatusFlag
capwapRadioOperStatusFlag.reference: Section 4.6.32. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioOperStatusFlag.description: Represents the operation status of a radio. The following values are supported: inoperable(0) - To indicate radio is inoperable, and capwapRadioFailureReason object will give reason in details, operable(1) - To indicate radio is operable.

capwapRadioFailureReason.name: capwapRadioFailureReason
capwapRadioFailureReason.reference: Section 4.6.32. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapRadioFailureReason.description: Represents errors caused by configuration operation. The following values are supported hwError(1) - Radio Failure, swError(2) - Software Failure, adminSet(3) - Administratively Set, unknown(8) - Unknown reason.

capwapJoinFailureReason.name: capwapJoinFailureReason
capwapJoinFailureReason.reference: Section 4.6.33. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapJoinFailureReason.description: The following join failure types are supported: unspecified(1) - unspecified failure reason, resDepletion(2) - Resource Depletion, unknownSource(3) - Unknown Source, incorrectData(4) - Incorrect Data, sessionInUse(5) - Session ID already in use, notSupportHw(6) - WTP Hardware not supported, notSupportBinding(7) - Binding Not Supported.

capwapImageFailureReason.name: capwapImageFailureReason
capwapImageFailureReason.reference: Section 4.6.33. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapImageFailureReason.description: The following software upgrade failure types are supported: invalidChecksum(1) - Invalid Checksum, invalidLength(2) - Invalid Data Length, other(3) - Other Error, inUse(4) - Image Already Present.

capwapConfigMsgErrorType.name: capwapConfigMsgErrorType
capwapConfigMsgErrorType.reference: Section 4.6.34. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapConfigMsgErrorType.description: The following software upgrade failure types are supported: unknownElement(1) - Unknown Message Element, unsupportedElement(2) - Unsupported Message Element, unknownValue(3) - Unknown Message Element Value, unsupportedValue(4) - Unsupported Message Element Value.

capwapMsgErrorElements.name: capwapMsgErrorElements
capwapMsgErrorElements.reference: Section 4.6.34. of CAPWAP Protocol Specification, RFC xxx.
capwapMsgErrorElements.description: Represents the message element sent by the AC in the Configuration Status Response message that caused the error.

capwapWTPStateGroup.name: capwapWTPStateGroup

capwapWTPsGroup.name: capwapWTPsGroup

capwapRadiosGroup.name: capwapRadiosGroup
capwapRadiosGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent wireless binding type, administrator status and operational status for radio.

capwapStationsGroup.name: capwapStationsGroup
capwapStationsGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used to represent stations' basic property.

capwapWTPsPhysicalGroup.name: capwapWTPsPhysicalGroup
capwapWTPsPhysicalGroup.description: Collection of objects that represent hardware information of WTP.

capwapWTPsLayer3Group.name: capwapWTPsLayer3Group
capwapWTPsLayer3Group.description: Collection of objects that represent layer3 information of WTP.

capwapWTPRebootStatsGroup.name: capwapWTPRebootStatsGroup
capwapWTPRebootStatsGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used for collecting WTP reboot count, link failure count, hardware failure count and so on.

capwapRadioStatsGroup.name: capwapRadioStatsGroup
capwapRadioStatsGroup.description: The collection of objects which are used for collecting radio reset count, channel change count, hardware failure count and so on

capwapNofificationGroup.name: capwapNofificationGroup
capwapNofificationGroup.description: Collection of notifications in this MIB.
